## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-102">W przypadku są odpowiednie <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> zdarzenia Przekaż wystąpienie <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> do programu obsługi dla skojarzonego zdarzenia.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-102">When they are raised, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> events pass an instance of  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> to  the handler for the associated event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> Pobiera właściwość nowy poziom audio danych wejściowych podczas obliczania <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> lub <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> zdarzenia.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> property gets the new level of audio input when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> event is raised.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-104">`AudioLevel` Właściwość <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> klasy zawiera bieżący poziom wejściowych danych audio do aparatu rozpoznawania mowy.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-104">The `AudioLevel` property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes provides the current level of the audio input to the speech recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-105">Poniższy przykład umożliwia dodanie obsługi zdarzeń do <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> obiektu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-105">The following example adds an event handler to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-106">Program obsługi generuje nowy poziom audio do konsoli.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-106">The handler outputs the new audio level to the console.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d1c9e-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> pochodną <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d1c9e-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the SpeechRecognitionEngine object.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add an event handler for the AudioLevelUpdated event.  
  sre.AudioLevelUpdated += new EventHandler<AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs>(sre_AudioLevelUpdated);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Write the audio level to the console when the AudioLevelUpdated event is raised.  
void sre_AudioLevelUpdated(object sender, AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs e)  
{  
  Console.WriteLine("The audio level is now: {0}.", e.AudioLevel);  
}  
  
```
